The hope by the presidential candidate of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP) in the 2019 general elections, Atiku Abubakar, to have access to the server of the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) was dashed on Monday when the Election Tribunal turned down his request, according to Channels TV. All five members of the Tribunal rejected Atiku’s application, arguing that the request could not be approved because of controversies surrounding the existence or otherwise of the server. The Tribunal is sitting in Abuja, Nigeria’s capital city. Details coming…